<p itemprop="description">A change and release manager coordinates and manages changes to IT systems and services. They ensure changes are implemented safely, efficiently, and with minimal risk to service availability and business operations.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage the change management process and change advisory board activities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Coordinate release planning and deployment activities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Assess change risks and implement risk mitigation strategies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure changes comply with governance and regulatory requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Coordinate with development and operations teams on release schedules</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Maintain change and release documentation and metrics</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Support incident resolution through emergency change processes</li>
    </ul>
</section>

